ISLAMABAD, Aug 2 (APP): In the run up to the fifth ‘Youm-e-Istehsal’, Foreign Secretary Muhammad Syrus Sajjad Qazi on Friday briefed the Islamabad-based diplomats on the situation in Indian Illegally Occupied Jammu and Kashmir.
In the meeting, he underscored the grave consequences of India’s actions of 5 August 2019 from the perspective of international law, human rights, and peace and security, a statement issued by the Foreign Office said.
